<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
This species is treated as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ching ex L. L. Xiang" authorityName="Ching ex L. L. Xiang" authorityYear="1994" box="[624,1139,295,320]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Polystichum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="daguanense">
<emphasis box="[624,904,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Polystichum daguanense</emphasis>
Ching ex L.L.Xiang
</taxonomicName>
by Zhu &amp; He (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kung, H. - S. &amp; Chu, W. - M. &amp; He, Z. - R. &amp; Zhang, L. - B." pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refId="ref3216" refString="Kung, H. - S., Chu, W. - M., He, Z. - R. &amp; Zhang, L. - B. (2001) Polystichum. Pp. 1 - 246 in Wu, C. - Y. (ed.), Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae. vol. 5 (2). ed. Kung, H. - S. Science Press, Beijing." type="journal volume" year="2001">
Kung 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
), however, the two taxa are different morphologically (Zhang &amp; Barrington, in press). They do not seem to be closely related.
</paragraph>
